Guinea Will Close All Foreign-Exchange Bureaus, State Television Reports

-- B y   O u g n a   C a m a r a
-- 
2011-03-10T03:47:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-09/guinea-cancels-nct-necotrans-of-france-s-port-deal-conde-says.html
  Guinea  will close all foreign-
exchange bureaus in the country as part of measures to regulate
the market and lower inflation,  Radio Television Guineenne 
reported.  A new mechanism is being established by the central bank to
regulate foreign-currency trade, the Conakry-based broadcaster
said, citing Prime Minister Mohamed Said Fofana.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ougna Camara in Conakry via Accra at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at   asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 